{
  "stem": "93.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And while I think of it, we landed in Omaha Beach in August of '44, not '45.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The war was over by '45.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the place where we ran into this first example of German brutality was a little town whose name escapes me at the moment.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But it was at the base of a hill called Montsec.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Apremont was the name of the town.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the Germans whom we had been chasing assembled all the men in the town, including male children and male babies, and executed them.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So when my regiment arrived at Apremont, we were greeted by a group of wailing and weeping women and a burning town.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "This was our first introduction to some of the bestiality the Germans were capable of.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "In any event, after the-- the Battle of the Bulge, the war, in essence, turned very rapidly in our favor, and we very quickly made our way to the Rhine River.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And my regiment crossed the Rhine River at Mainz on March the 26th, 1945.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We did this in assault boats.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We suffered some very severe casualties in so doing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But when we got on the other side, the German resistance virtually collapsed.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And in short order, we captured the city of Wiesbaden.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Now, from Wiesbaden, we turned north and went to the city of Kassel, which at the time was a manufacturing city with a population of perhaps 100,000, 150,000 people.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And one of the things that was really strange about this is as we were fighting for Kassel, we kept knocking out German tanks, and they kept reappearing.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And it turned out that there was a tank factory in the city of Kassel, and there was a German tank school in the city of Erfurt, which was to the east.",
      "word_count": 32
    }
  ],
